    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL AIR SUSPENSION WITH TAPERED LEAF SPRINGS - CAB AIR RELEASE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CAB AIR RELEASE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>Cab air release controls permit the driver to deflate the air springs from the cab when hooking up to
                a trailer. For normal operation the "air suspension cab control valve" will be in the RUN position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300107">Figure 7</hotlnk>). To dump the air from the springs, place the valve in the
                DUMP position. The switch has a guard to prevent an unintentional air dump.
                <emph type="bold">Do not remove the guard.</emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="f0300107" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300107" filename="../figg03/G0300107.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Cab Controls</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
